data.name: DateTimeZoneType_Description
data.value: Represents a time zone - a mapping between UTC and local time. A time zone maps UTC instants to local times - or, equivalently, to the offset from UTC at any particular instant.

data.name: DurationType_Description
data.value: Represents a fixed (and calendar-independent) length of time.

data.name: InstantType_Description
data.value: Represents an instant on the global timeline, with nanosecond resolution.

data.name: IsoDayOfWeekType_Description
data.value: Equates the days of the week with their numerical value according to ISO-8601. Monday = 1, Tuesday = 2, Wednesday = 3, Thursday = 4, Friday = 5, Saturday = 6, Sunday = 7.

data.name: LocalDateTimeType_Description
data.value: A date and time in a particular calendar system.

data.name: LocalDateType_Description
data.value: LocalDate is an immutable struct representing a date within the calendar, with no reference to a particular time zone or time of day.

data.name: LocalTimeType_Description
data.value: LocalTime is an immutable struct representing a time of day, with no reference to a particular calendar, time zone or date.

data.name: OffsetDateTimeType_Description
data.value: A local date and time in a particular calendar system, combined with an offset from UTC.

data.name: OffsetDateType_Description
data.value: A combination of a LocalDate and an Offset, to represent a date at a specific offset from UTC but without any time-of-day information.

data.name: OffsetTimeType_Description
data.value: A combination of a LocalTime and an Offset, to represent a time-of-day at a specific offset from UTC but without any date information.

data.name: OffsetType_Description
data.value: An offset from UTC in seconds. A positive value means that the local time is ahead of UTC (e.g. for Europe); a negative value means that the local time is behind UTC (e.g. for America).

data.name: PeriodType_Description
data.value: Represents a period of time expressed in human chronological terms: hours, days, weeks, months and so on.

data.name: ZonedDateTimeType_Description
data.value: A LocalDateTime in a specific time zone and with a particular offset to distinguish between otherwise-ambiguous instants. A ZonedDateTime is global, in that it maps to a single Instant.

data.name: NodaTime_NoPatternProvided
data.value: The provided patterns are empty. You must provide at least one pattern for type {0}.
